ej,greea001,M,culbf901,Arguing hit by pitch $San Diego manager Green ejected by 3b umpire Culbreth for strange sequence of events; pitch to Chirinos hit the knob of his bat and rolled to the pitcher, who threw him out; plate umpire Blakney called it a dead ball; manager Green argued it to be either a ball in play or a hit by pitch, that there was way it could be a dead ball; the play was not reviewable so Green asked the umpires to huddle and overturn the call; they refused and the Rangers challenged the call, claiming Chirinos was hit by the pitch; the call was overturned to hit by pitch, causing a tirade by Green that led to his ejection
